{
  "_README": [
    "NSE/BSE trading holidays. Rename this file to nse_holidays.json to",
    "activate. You MUST verify these dates against the SEBI/NSE official",
    "'List of Trading Holidays' circular before use — published yearly in",
    "December of the prior year.",
    "Source of truth: https://www.nseindia.com/resources/exchange-communication-holidays",
    "(URL provided for the operator to verify against; do NOT have Claude",
    "fetch it programmatically — these dates change yearly and may shift",
    "if a holiday falls on a weekend.)",
    "Only dates listed here will be skipped by trading_days_between(...).",
    "Weekends are filtered separately and need no entries.",
    "",
    "Two flavours of dates appear below — they have different maintenance",
    "obligations on the operator:",
    "  * FIXED-RECURRING: date is the same calendar day every year.",
    "    Only re-check when that date falls on a Sat/Sun (NSE may then",
    "    declare a substitute trading-holiday on the adjacent weekday).",
    "    Members of this set: Republic Day (Jan 26), Maharashtra Day",
    "    (May 1), Independence Day (Aug 15), Mahatma Gandhi Jayanti",
    "    (Oct 2), Christmas (Dec 25). The annotations below mark each.",
    "  * FESTIVAL-SHIFTING: lunar/solar-calendar dates that move yearly.",
    "    MUST be re-verified each year against the official NSE circular.",
    "    Members of this set: Mahashivratri, Holi, Eid-ul-Fitr, Ram",
    "    Navami / Mahavir Jayanti, Good Friday, Ganesh Chaturthi, Diwali",
    "    Laxmi Pujan, Diwali Balipratipada, Prakash Gurpurb, etc."
  ],
